Comcast is opening its Xfinity Stores nationwide at 8:00 a.m. local time on September 22 in all of its markets to enable consumers to purchase the new iPhone 8 and iPhone 8 Plus. Xfinity Internet customers who activate a new Xfinity Mobile line in stores can get the next generation iPhone from Apple, and also trade in their qualifying devices and receive a check for the value of that device within 30 days.

iPhone 8 and iPhone 8 Plus are a new generation of iPhone featuring a new glass and aluminum design
